Glad this business is open and serving the community during COVID. But customer service is terrible. Workers don't pay attention to the names on pickup orders. No manager in sight, basically no one is in charge and staff do the best they can, but it's an unsupervised free for all.  The food is good, the cook stations are well trained, probably thanks to the strict, easy to follow instructions on the monitors. But the cashiers, the staff who interact with customers, the ones holding pickup orders hostage behind the counter - they are unprofessional, rude, and downright terrible.  My order was supposed to be ready at 6:30pm. I arrived at 6:40pm and asked if it was ready. They told me no, it's being made. I asked at 6:50pm, and 7:00pm, they told me there's other orders. At 7:10pm, they told me they have no record of the order. I gave them the name several times, and then I gave them the confirmation # and they finally found the order. When I asked why I had to wait 40 minutes for them to figure out my orders been ready on the counter, just sitting there, the cashier ignored me and moved onto the next customer. Absolutely disgusting. I understand it's a stressful time, but this is way below standard. Simply unacceptable.

I usually get my food very very quick even if the line is long. The cashiers are ALWAYS very friendly.  It is very neat to see the cooks preparing the food right behind the glass counter. They always look like they're working the hardest of the group of workers.  I don't understand the point of having many people crammed into the area where they prepare the meals. Sometimes there will be 3 or 4 workers behind the glass preparing meals and 1 or 2 of them are the only ones working efficiently. The others look overwhelmed and hop around from customer to customer even when it is not very busy.  The tables are usually not clean but they're also not too dirty. Also, there is always at least one comfortable spot available to sit somehow, even when it seems busy.  Sometimes the food will come out VERY salty as if salt was poured into the pot and wasnt stirred all the way through.  I am nitpicking because I come here often. It has its cons but I enjoy coming here because this place is fantastic for when I am short on time and I need to order something filling and satifying.
